# Project Guidelines

Always refer to the relevant guideline files in `guidelines/` before making changes. Don't limit to one — cross-reference as needed.

- **coding.md** — general coding practices (always apply)
- **application.md** — application-specific rules (always apply)
- **frontend.md** — React structure, styling (shadcn/ui, Tailwind), UX (apply for frontend tasks)
- **backend.md** — Prisma, services, transactions (apply for backend tasks)
- **security.md** — OWASP, input sanitisation, no console.log (apply whenever touching user-facing or data logic)

When doing a **code review**, put ✅/❌ next to each guideline item and output a full report.
